            "text": "{\"activities\": [{\"id\":17716512160000,\"performer\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"user_id\":82007884864},\"highlight\":36,\"ticket_id\":18125250,\"performed_at\":\"2026-02-21T05:20:16Z\",\"actions\":[{\"type\":\"note\",\"content\":{\"body\":\"<div>Knowledge Base Summary : <b>Bot: </b> </div>\\n<div>Hello Rishika Biswakarma!</div>\\n<br><div><strong>Do you have ticket ID for this concern? </strong></div>\\n<br><b>Customer: </b> Yes<br><b>Bot: </b> &#127991; Enter the ticket ID associated with the issue<br><b>Customer: </b> 18125250<br><b>Bot: </b> Please select the query type<br><b>Customer: </b> RazorAgent  &#129302;<br><b>Bot: </b> Type your query<br><b>Customer: </b> transaction limit<br><b>Bot: </b> To increase your transaction limit, please follow these steps:<br><br>1. Navigate to the Account and Settings section on your dashboard.<br>2. Go to Payments and refunds.<br>3. Select Transaction limits.<br>4. Click on the pencil option on the right corner of the option Limit per domestic transaction.<br>5. Update the relevant fields and submit the request for verification.<br><br>This request will be routed to the relevant team (risk team) for a check and either approval or rejection. If you have already raised a request and it has breached the TAT (more than 3-4 working days), please follow up with the Risk team.<br><b>Bot: </b> Please find the recommended article(s)<br><i>[Customer Feedback: Was this helpful? - Yes]</i><br><div>1. Increase transaction limit</div>\\n<div>2. Transaction failure</div>\\n<div>3. How to track a transaction</div>\\n<b>Bot: </b> The code has been generated successfully : <strong>4lX5buH0HX4D &#128273;</strong><br>\",\"body_text\":\"Knowledge Base Summary : Bot:   Hello Rishika Biswakarma!   Do you have ticket ID for this concern?   Customer:  Yes Bot:  ? Enter the ticket ID associated with the issue Customer:  18125250 Bot:  Please select the query type Customer:  RazorAgent  ? Bot:  Type your query Customer:  transaction limit Bot:  To increase your transaction limit, please follow these steps:  1. Navigate to the Account and Settings section on your dashboard. 2. Go to Payments and refunds. 3. Select Transaction limits. 4. Click on the pencil option on the right corner of the option Limit per domestic transaction. 5. Update the relevant fields and submit the request for verification.  This request will be routed to the relevant team (risk team) for a check and either approval or rejection. If you have already raised a request and it has breached the TAT (more than 3-4 working days), please follow up with the Risk team. Bot:  Please find the recommended article(s) [Customer Feedback: Was this helpful? - Yes]  1. Increase transaction limit  2. Transaction failure  3. How to track a transaction Bot:  The code has been generated successfully : 4lX5buH0HX4D ?\",\"structured_body\":null,\"id\":83226918032,\"incoming\":false,\"private\":true,\"user_id\":82007884864,\"support_email\":null,\"source\":2,\"category\":2,\"to_emails\":[],\"from_email\":null,\"cc_emails\":[],\"bcc_emails\":null,\"email_failure_count\":null,\"outgoing_failures\":null,\"thread_id\":null,\"thread_message_id\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-21T05:20:16Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-21T05:20:16Z\",\"last_edited_at\":null,\"last_edited_user_id\":null,\"attachments\":[],\"automation_id\":null,\"automation_type_id\":null,\"automation_channel_type\":null,\"auto_response\":false,\"ticket_id\":18125250,\"threading_type\":null,\"delivery_details\":{\"failed_emails\":[],\"pending_emails\":[]},\"deleted\":false,\"cloud_files\":[],\"has_quoted_text\":false}}]},{\"id\":17716485524045,\"performer\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"user_id\":82164113806},\"highlight\":7,\"ticket_id\":18125250,\"performed_at\":\"2026-02-21T04:35:52Z\",\"actions\":[{\"type\":\"property_update\",\"content\":{\"responder_id\":82218776560}}]},{\"id\":17716484114229,\"performer\":{\"type\":\"system\",\"system\":{\"id\":0,\"type\":\"default_system\",\"name\":\"\",\"exi